@{ ViewBag.Title = "About"; }

<div id="about">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1>about</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="page-header">
            <h2>what is this?</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
            compilify.net is an interactive web interface for the .NET compiler 
            powered by the <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/roslyn">Roslyn Project</a>. 
            It allows you to quickly and easily execute snippets of C# code from 
            your browser.
        </p>
        <div class="page-header">
            <h2>why would I use this?</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
            You can use compilify.net to learn C#, share and test code, reproduce bugs, explore fixes, and to 
            demonstrate and collaborate on ideas. It's fast and simple. You can use it from any device* with a web 
            browser, without installing any additional plugins. Use it when you don't have time for a full IDE!
        </p>
        <p class="disclaimer">
            * This site has not yet been tested on all devices. If you find a bug,
            <a href="https://github.com/Compilify/Compilify/issues">let us know</a>!
        </p>
        <div class="page-header">
            <h2>how do I use this?</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
            Type or paste your code in the editor and click run. At the end of your code, return the value you want to 
            display in the results panel below. Click the save link to generate a unique URL for your snippet. 
        </p>
        <p>
            Check out these cool examples:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="//compilify.net/3b">FizzBuzz</a></li>
            <li><a href="//compilify.net/8m/2">Fibonacci Sequence</a></li>
            <li><a href="//compilify.net/pm/6">Slug Generator</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Have an awesome snippet to share? <a href="https://github.com/Compilify/Compilify/issues/24" target="_blank">
            Submit your snippet</a> for use as an example!
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="http://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Forums/en-US/roslyn/thread/f5adeaf0-49d0-42dc-861b-0f6ffd731825">
            Not all features</a> of the compiler are currently supported by the 
            Roslyn CTP.
        </p>
        <div class="page-header">
            <h2>can I help?</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
            Absolutely! The source code for this site is available 
            on <a href="https://github.com/Compilify/Compilify">Github</a> under the 
            <a href="https://github.com/Compilify/Compilify/blob/master/LICENSE">
            MIT license</a>! 
        </p>
        <div class="page-header">
            <h3>who are you?</h3>
        </div>
        <p>
            This project was built by <a href="https://twitter.com/jrusbatch" title="Justin Rusbatch">@@jrusbatch</a>
            and <a href="https://twitter.com/fekberg" title="Filip Ekberg">@@fekberg</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>